The '''chest''' is a thievable chest in the [[Isle of Souls Dungeon]] that requires level 28 [[Thieving]] to steal from. Each chest yields 150 [[experience]], and the chest's loot respawns instantly. These chests are the only ones where players can obtain a [[dark key]], which is used to loot the [[Dark Chest]] in the [[Crumbling Tower]] basement.

Upon failing to loot the chest, there is a 1 in 6 chance (after failing thieving roll){{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1450810611877793794|date=20 October 2021|archiveurl=https://archive.md/od3cd|archivedate=4 November 2021|quote=1/6 if you failed the thieving roll.}} to get teleported north-east of the dungeon entrance. Carrying a [[lockpick]] increases the rate at which players successfully pick the lock of these chests.

In order to save inventory space when looting the chest, it is recommended to bring a [[gem bag]] and [[herb sack]].

